\begin_layout Subsection
Background
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Africa is to see rapid development in the coming decades - but the phenomenal
 growth prospects of African countries is not withouth the kind of political
 risks that exist in South and South-East Asia.
 The proposed study aims to provide aims to assess the recent growth of
 African countries (more particularly the countries : Kenya, Ethiopia) in
 relation to Asian countries - with respect to utility and demand elasticities.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The wider goal of the project is finding out spending patterns and their
 control by the societies.
 Despite the possibility of dramatic change, social attitudes are slow to
 detect and change at a differential pace
