\begin_layout Subsection
Observations
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
1.
 It is found that advertising elasticity is equal or higher during recession
 than in expansion (it being higher or lower in developing countries should
 fit within this framework).
 Possible reasons (i) advertising clutter is lower due to cutbacks in advertisin
g; (ii) consumers pay better attention to ad messages or (iii) ad budgets
 are supported by higher price and promotional incentives.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
2.
 Comparison of means reveals that durable goods have the highest advertising
 elasticity, followed by pharmaceuticals and service goods.
 Short-run advertising elasticity is higher for products in the early stage
 of the life cycle than those in the mature stage.
\end_layout

